  "prompt": "What does Obama's mother-in-law do all day in the White House?",
  "response": "During her time in the White House, Michelle Obama's mother, Marian Robinson, played an important role in the First Family's daily life, primarily focusing on supporting her family and helping to care for her granddaughters, Malia and Sasha Obama. While she did not have any official responsibilities or duties, she contributed to the household by providing a sense of stability and normalcy for her granddaughters amidst the unique environment of living in the White House. Marian Robinson's presence was valued for the continuity and additional support she offered as the family adjusted to their new life.",
